(21, 'Home', 10, 4, 'home', 'journal-of-andrology-gynaecology', '<p>Journal of Andrology &amp; Gynecology deals with the disorders and complications that are related to the male and female reproductive systems respectively. The current research in Andrology and Gynecology involves the development of new techniques to minimize these ailments and provides knowledge for researchers, practitioners and even for common people.</p><div class="ic-value"><b>IC Value: <a href="http://jml2012.indexcopernicus.com/Journal+of+Andrology+and+Gynaecology,p24783001,3.html" target="_blank">65.53</a></b></div><p><span style="color: #cc5200;"><strong>Editor-in-Chief</strong></span></p><table border="1" width="650" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1"><tbody><tr><td><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-3420" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/mari_giancarlo.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Giancarlo Mari</strong> is the Chair of the Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology at the University of Tennessee Health Science Center. His research interests are fetal anemia, fetal doppler ultrasound, fetal growth, fetal therapy, intra-uterine-growth restriction, maternal-fetal medicine, obstetrics and gynecology.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><font size="3" color="#CC5200"><strong>Indexed in: </strong></font></p><p><li><a href="http://journalseek.net/cgi-bin/journalseek/journalsearch.cgi?query=2332-3442&amp;field=title&amp;editorID=&amp;send=Search+Title%2FISSN+Only" target="_blank">Genamics JournalSeek</a></li></p><p><li><a href="http://jml2012.indexcopernicus.com/Journal+of+Andrology+and+Gynaecology,p24783001,3.html" target="_blank">Index Copernicus</a></li></p><p><li><a href="http://www.worldcat.org/title/journal-of-andrology-gynaecology/oclc/863697029&amp;referer=brief_results" target="_blank">WorldCat</a></li></p><p><li><a href="http://www.icmje.org/journals-following-the-icmje-recommendations/" target="_blank">ICMJE</a></li></p><p><li><a href="http://www.sherpa.ac.uk/romeo/search.php?source=journal&amp;sourceid=30020&amp;la=en&amp;fIDnum=|&amp;mode=simple " target="_blank">SHERPA/RoMEO</a></li></p><p><li><a href="http://journalseeker.researchbib.com/view/issn/2332-3442" target="_blank">Research Bible</a></li></p><p><li><a href="http://sciforum.net/statistics/publisher/journals/2388" target="_blank">Sciforum </a></li></p><p><li><a href="http://jgateplus.com/search/footer-html/PublisherPartners.jsp" target="_blank">J-Gate</a></li></p><p><li><a href="https://scholar.google.co.in/scholar?hl=en&amp;q=avensonline.org&amp;btnG= " target="_blank">Google Scholar</a></li></p><p><li><a href="http://jandc.pubshub.com/Home" target="_blank">PubsHub</a></li></p><p><li><a href="http://www.academickeys.com/">AcademicKeys</a></li></p><p><li><a href="http://www.drji.org/BrowseAllJournals.aspx" target="_blank">Directory of Research Journals Indexing</a></li></p><p><li><a href="http://miar.ub.edu/" target="_blank">MIAR</a></li></p><p> <br/> <br/> <br/> <br/> </p>', '2016-10-01', '2016-10-01', 1),
(22, 'Aims Scope', 10, 4, 'aims-scope', 'journal-of-andrology-gynaecology', '<p>Journal of Andrology &amp; Gynecology deals with the disorders and complications that are related to the male and female reproductive systems respectively. The current research in Andrology and Gynecology involves the development of new techniques to minimize these ailments and provides knowledge for researchers, practitioners and even for common people.</p><p>Topics covered in this Journal include, but are not limited to:</p><p><li>Male &amp; Female Sexual and Reproductive Health</li></p><p><li>Advanced Cellular and Molecular Mechanisms</li></p><p><li>Histopathological Ailments and Treatment</li></p><p><li>Male &amp; Female-Aging</li></p><p><li>Surgical Breakthroughs</li></p><p><li>Infertility</li></p><p><li>Prenatal Diagnosis</li></p><p><li>Maternal-Fetal Medicine &amp; Care</li></p><p><li>Female Genital Tract Cancers</li></p><p><li>Uterine Tumours Ovarian Cancer</li></p><p><li>Female Urology</li></p><p><li>Clinical Andrology &amp; Gynecology</li></p><p><li>Female Contraception</li></p><p><li>Coagulation Disorders in Pregnancy</li></p><p><li>Minimally Invasive Surgical approaches for Gynecological Problems</li></p><p><li>Pregnancy Complications </li></p><p><li>Use of Advanced Technology for Child Birth</li></p><p><li>Gynecological Diseases</li></p><p><li>Embryology</li></p><p><li>Urinary Tract Infections </li></p><p><li>Antenatal Care and Assessment</li></p><p><li>Molecular Genetics in  Gynaecology</li></p><p><li>Case Reports</li></p>', '2016-10-01', '2016-10-01', 1),
(23, 'Editorial Board', 10, 4, 'editorial-board', 'journal-of-andrology-gynaecology', '<div class="eb-box"><span style="color: #cc5200;"><strong>Editor-in-Chief</strong></span><p></p><table border="1" width="650" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1"><tbody><tr><td><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-3420" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/mari_giancarlo.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Giancarlo Mari</strong> is the Chair of the Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology at the University of Tennessee Health Science Center, USA. His research interests are fetal anemia, fetal doppler ultrasound, fetal growth, fetal therapy, intra-uterine-growth restriction, maternal-fetal medicine, obstetrics and gynecology.</p></div></td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-2911" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/ernie-abel.png" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Ernest L Abel</strong> is a Professor in the Department of Obstetrics &amp; Gynecology, School of Medicine and professor of Psychology in the School of Social Science at Wayne State University, USA. He is a past president of two international societies, the Behavioral Teratology Society and the Fetal Alcohol Study Group and has been honored as a “distinguished faculty” at Wayne State.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-2761" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/harris1.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Harris E. Foster Jr</strong> is a Professor of Urology in the Yale Univesity School of Medicine and Chief of Urology for the Veteran’s Administration Medical Center Connecticut, USA. He has written extensively in urology and has been involved in or chaired a number of multicenter randomized clinical trials involving various male and female urological disorders.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-12845" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Dr-Kamal-Shaeer-photo.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Kamal Zaki Mahmoud Shaeer</strong> is a Professor of Reproductive Medicine and Andrology, Faculty of Medicine at Cairo University, Eygpt. His research focuses on Erectile Dysfunction, male infertility, assisted fertilization, Andrology, reproductive and sexual Medicine.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-12813" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Joanne-Kwak-Kim-MD-300-dpi-1.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Kwak-Kim</strong> is a Professor of Obstetrics and Gynecology and Microbiology and Immunology of Rosalind Franklin University of Medicine and Science, as well as the Assistant Chair, Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology at the Chicago Medical School, USA. Currently, she serves as Director of the Reproductive Medicine Center. Her interest lies in Reproductive Immunology; particularly, recurrent pregnancy loss.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-23079" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/Rajiv-Mahendru.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Rajiv Mahendru</strong> is a Professor and Head, Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology in BPS Government Medical College, India. He has 41 Publications in reputed journals and is the recipient of a prestigious Award for excellence in Medical field. He has chaired numerous sessions in the National &amp; International conferences.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-12700" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/H-Sadri-Ardekani-1.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Hooman Sadri-Ardekani</strong> is an Assistant Professor at Avicenna Research Institute (ARI), Tehran, Iran. His research focuses on fertility preservation in high risk patients, human Spermatogonial Stem Cell, clinical Andrology, medical genetics, family planning and reproductive health care and medical education.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-4691" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Badawy-Shawky-5X7.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Shawky Badawy</strong> is a Director in the Division of Reproductive Endocrinology /Infertility and Professor of the Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology at Upstate Medical University, USA. His research focuses on Endometriosis, infertility management, menstrual dysfunction, laparoscopic and hysteroscopic surgery, and microsurgery.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-10059" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/YKE-Photo.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Youqiang Ke</strong> is a Director of the Molecular Pathology Laboratory and professor in the Department of Molecular and Clinical Cancer Medicine of the University of Liverpool in England, UK. His research group works on investigations of the molecular mechanisms involved in malignant progression of cancer cells, mainly in prostate cancer.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-10064" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/billede-sdu.png" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Lars Lund</strong> is a Professor in the Department of Urology, Odense University Hospital and at Southern University of Denmark, UK. His research focuses on urological cancers, cryo-ablation (freezing) of cancer especially in the kidney and prostate, shock wave treatment (ESWT/L) for e.g. impotence, andrology laparoscopic surgery, education and training of young doctors.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft 