es Female Urology, Neurourology and Urodynamics.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-4181" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/desouza.png" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. DeSouza</strong> is an Associate Director for the Residency Program and Medical Director of the University of Texas Physicians Urology Clinic, USA. Her research interests include reconstructive and female urology, endolaparoscopy and general urology including: benign prostatic hyperplasia, urinary incontinence and kidney stones.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-9865" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/cevdetweb.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Cevdet kaya</strong> is an Associate Professor in the Department of Urology at Marmara University and urology specialist at Haydarpasa Numune Training and Research Hospital, Turkey. His area of expertise includes pediatric urology, urooncology, and erectile dysfunction.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-10390" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/biong-bo1.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Bo-Ying Bao</strong> is an Associate Professor in the Department of Pharmacy at China Medical University, Taiwan. His research interest focuses on the discovery of biomarkers able to improve the management of prostate cancer.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-4306" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Oehler.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Martin Oehler</strong> is an Associate Professor and Director of Gynaecological Oncology at the Royal Adelaide Hospital, Australia. His research interests include the development of novel molecular approaches to ovarian cancer diagnosis and treatment, and minimally invasive surgery including robotic surgery for gynaecological cancer and complex benign gynaecological disease.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-9573" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/xiao.png" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Xiao Gu</strong> is an Associate Professor in the Department of Urology at Yangzhou University, China. His clinical experience includes renal transplantation and all types of urologic disease, including pediatric urology. He has extensive research experience in organ transplantation and the mechanisms of invasiveness and metastasis of transitional cell carcinoma of bladder.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-12554" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Awaiting1.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Domenico Canale</strong> is Head of Andrology unit and an Assistant Professor in the School of Endocrinology and Gynecology at University of Pisa Medical School, Italy. His research fields are Andrology, Molecular Human Reproduction, Sexual Medicine and Clinical Endocrinology.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-12521" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Duancheng-Wen.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Duancheng Wen</strong> serves as an Assistant Research Professor of Ronald O. Perleman and Claudia Cohen Center for Reproductive Medicine at the Weill Cornell Medical College, USA. His research interest focuses on gametogenesis, embryogenesis, nuclear reprogramming and embryonic stem cells.</p></div><div class="eb-box"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-9585" title="" src="http://www.avensonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/shapiro.jpg" alt="" width="100" height="100"/><p></p><p><strong>Dr. Robert Shapiro</strong> is an Assistant Clinical Professor of Obstetrics and Gynecology at 